\b\f2 Mailing a Message}{\f2 
\par 
\par You can use WinVN to send an }{\f2\ul electronic mail message}{\v\f2 electronic_mail_message}{\f2  either as a personal reply to the author of an article, or as an independent message.  
\par 
\par A message contains a }{\f2\ul header}{\v\f2 header}{\f2  followed by the text of the message.  A message is directed to one or more }{\f2 recipients}{\f2  by a "To:" line in the header.  If you want to send a message to more than one person, type the elec
tronic mail addresses of the recipients on the "To:" line, separated by commas.  The text of a message is separated from the header by a blank line.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2 Reply Messages
\par }{\f2 
\par A reply message has the same "Subject:" line as the article which inspired it.  (The notation "Re:" is added.)   Also, a reply message typically selectively quotes the article which inspired it, to give some context to the recipient.
\par 
\par You start composing a reply message by selecting the }{\b\f2 via Mail}{\f2  option of an }{\f2\uldb article window's}{\v\f2 article_window}{\f2  }{\b\f2 Respond}{\f2  menu.  See }{\f2\uldb Respond Menu Commands}{\v\f2 respond_menu_commands}{\f2 .  WinVN c
reates a }{\f2\uldb mail window}{\v\f2 mail_window}{\f2 .  The }{\f2\ul header}{\v\f2 header}{\f2  of the message in this window is filled in with information taken from WinVN configuration options and from the header of the referenced article.  (See }{
\f2\uldb Configuring WinVN}{\v\f2 configuring_winvn}{\f2 .)  The full text of the referenced article is also included in this window, with each line preceded by a "}{\b\f2 >}{\f2 " to indicate that an article is being quoted.  
\par 
\par Fill in the text of your message.  You should delete irrelevant quoted lines. 
\par 
\par }{\b\f2 New Messages
\par }{\f2 
\par You start composing a "brand new" message--one that does not reference an article--by selecting the }{\b\f2 Compose mail message}{\f2  option from the }{\b\f2 Optionss}{\f2  menu of the }{\f2\uldb main window}{\v\f2 main_window}{\f2 .  (See }{\f2\uldb Op
tions Menu Commands}{\v\f2 options_menu_commands}{\f2 .)  WinVN creates a }{\f2\uldb mail}{\f2\uldb  window}{\v\f2 mail_window}{\f2  for your new article.  Your name and organization are filled in based on the way you configured WinVN.
\par 
\par You must fill in an appropriate subject for the new article on the "Subject:" line, and a recipient on the "To:" line.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2 Sending the Message
\par }{\f2 
\par When you have completed composing your message, you can send it or cancel it.  See }{\f2\uldb Mail Menu Commands}{\v\f2 mail_menu_commands}{\f2 .  After you have sent the message, you can close the mail window.\page 
